      • empty

        private void empty()
        empty? ( id -- be ) check! ."EMPTY" = ; compare a String from the top of the stack with the literal value "EMPTY". If they are equal, put true on the stack. Else, put false on the stack"

      • send

        private void send()
        send! ( s v -- b ) send a value v to team-member s; returns a boolean indicating success or failure. Failure can occur if the robot is dead (health = 0), or its mailbox is full.

        public void evaluateAllForthWords(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> allForthWords,
                                  int counter)

        Parameters:
